lmstudioCode.mcpServers.markdownDescription:
MCP (Model Context Protocol) servers to make available to the agent, as a map of `name → server`. Each server is either a local (stdio) command or a remote (http/sse) URL.

Servers configured for **Claude Code** (`.mcp.json` at the workspace root) and **VS Code Copilot** (`.vscode/mcp.json` and the user `mcp` setting) are also discovered automatically — use this setting to add servers specific to LM Studio Code, or to override a discovered one. Entries here take precedence on a name collision.

Local (stdio) example:
```json
{
  "playwright": { "command": "npx", "args": ["-y", "@playwright/mcp@latest"] }
}
```
Remote (http/sse) example:
```json
{
  "docs": { "type": "http", "url": "https://example.com/mcp", "headers": { "Authorization": "Bearer ${MY_TOKEN}" } }
}
```
`${VAR}` references are resolved from the environment before launch. Set `"enabled": false` to keep a server defined but off. Note: each MCP server adds its tool schemas to the model's context, which is limited on local models — enable only what you need.
